570
00:44:03.424 --> 00:44:04.720
You just broke a rib.

571
00:44:04.924 --> 00:44:07.550
- It was great to see you.
- It was great seeing you too.


572
00:44:08.990 --> 00:44:14.753
She's great, man. I'll dig some more.
Give you a call tomorrow.


573
00:44:14.957 --> 00:44:17.480
You think you could sit
on those hands till then?


574
00:44:17.691 --> 00:44:18.714
- Done.
- All right.


575
00:44:18.924 --> 00:44:21.152
- All right.
- Nice being with you. See you, Rosie.


576
00:44:21.357 --> 00:44:22.755
See you.

577
00:44:25.424 --> 00:44:26.412
Come in.

578
00:44:28.758 --> 00:44:30.155
- Hey.
- Hey.


579
00:44:30.357 --> 00:44:33.187
<i>To Kill a Mockingbird's on 46.
You wanna watch?</i>


580
00:44:33.391 --> 00:44:35.323
Thanks. I'll be out in a minute.

581
00:44:36.090 --> 00:44:37.181
Finish that report yet?

582
00:44:37.924 --> 00:44:39.049
Not yet.

583
00:44:46.990 --> 00:44:49.047
Where did you dig this up?
This was years ago.


584
00:44:50.491 --> 00:44:52.956
- Internet.
- Internet.


585
00:44:54.457 --> 00:44:58.412
Why did they question you
if he was killed in jail?


586
00:44:58.624 --> 00:45:00.089
Well, you know..

587
00:45:00.291 --> 00:45:03.155
sometimes people think the police
can do anything they want.


588
00:45:03.357 --> 00:45:04.789
That's not the case.

589
00:45:04.990 --> 00:45:07.752
They questioned us,
nothing came of it.


590
00:45:08.957 --> 00:45:11.014
What was his name?

591
00:45:11.224 --> 00:45:12.281
The man who did it.

592
00:45:12.491 --> 00:45:14.684
It only says "inmate."

593
00:45:19.724 --> 00:45:20.950
I just wanna know.

594
00:45:23.624 --> 00:45:26.419
I told you a hundred times.
Daniel Hill.


595
00:45:26.624 --> 00:45:28.783
He can't hurt us anymore.

596
00:45:53.357 --> 00:45:57.619
I've driven by this church
a thousand times and never came in.


597
00:45:57.823 --> 00:45:59.914
It's lovely.

598
00:46:00.124 --> 00:46:01.112
It's private.

599
00:46:02.391 --> 00:46:04.380
So were you followed?

600
00:46:05.591 --> 00:46:07.988
Who would be following me?

601
00:46:08.190 --> 00:46:12.623
- You wearing a wire?
- No. Are you?


602
00:46:19.524 --> 00:46:21.513
Why were you watching me
yesterday?


603
00:46:21.724 --> 00:46:24.155
Do you have something to tell me?

604
00:46:24.357 --> 00:46:26.050
Ask you.

605
00:46:27.157 --> 00:46:29.055
Why haven't you told
the police about me?


606
00:46:29.257 --> 00:46:31.519
I don't trust the police.

607
00:46:31.724 --> 00:46:34.417
Look, I know your husband
was talking to the DA.


608
00:46:34.624 --> 00:46:36.556
He was gonna testify
against Robert Vaughn.


609
00:46:36.758 --> 00:46:40.212
So I need to know
who else he was gonna implicate.


610
00:46:42.090 --> 00:46:44.113
Did you clean my house?

611
00:46:45.124 --> 00:46:48.056
Look, Mr. Cutler,
this has to be a two-way street.


612
00:46:48.257 --> 00:46:50.746
I haven't gone to the police
and I'm not about to.


613
00:46:50.957 --> 00:46:55.889
But, please, I need to know
what happened for myself.


614
00:46:59.057 --> 00:47:01.921
I used to come to this church
twice a week.


615
00:47:02.124 --> 00:47:05.886
Once for Mass, once for confession.

616
00:47:09.823 --> 00:47:12.688
That was a long time ago.

617
00:47:15.591 --> 00:47:16.988
Yes.

618
00:47:18.291 --> 00:47:19.847
Yeah, I cleaned your house.

619
00:47:22.924 --> 00:47:25.584
- Oh, God.
- Looked like a legitimate crime scene.


620
00:47:26.257 --> 00:47:28.280
Whoever did it had access
to the materials..


621
00:47:28.491 --> 00:47:30.514
and they knew procedure.

622
00:47:31.558 --> 00:47:33.785
- How did he..?
- He was shot.


623
00:47:36.090 --> 00:47:37.283
Where, exactly?

624
00:47:37.790 --> 00:47:41.018
Living room. On the couch.

625
00:47:42.090 --> 00:47:44.056
Who hired you?

626
00:47:44.691 --> 00:47:47.657
That's what I'm trying to find out,
Mrs. Norcut.


627
00:47:48.658 --> 00:47:51.488
- Two-way street, right?
- Yeah.


628
00:47:52.291 --> 00:47:55.382
What was your husband
going to tell the grand jury?


629
00:48:00.324 --> 00:48:03.778
I think it's better if I show you.

630
00:48:04.291 --> 00:48:09.053
This used to be an old fire station,
and now it's a safe haven for kids.


631
00:48:13.924 --> 00:48:16.152
That's a mighty big pair of scissors.

632
00:48:16.357 --> 00:48:17.845
Oh, that's Robert Vaughn.

633
00:48:18.057 --> 00:48:21.251
He did the initial fundraising.
Without him, we wouldn't be here.


634
00:48:22.624 --> 00:48:24.987
My office is upstairs.

635
00:48:33.990 --> 00:48:36.888
John wrote everything by hand
so that it could be authenticated.


636
00:48:37.090 --> 00:48:40.545
He called this his
"get out of jail free card."


637
00:48:40.757 --> 00:48:41.848
What is it?

638
00:48:42.057 --> 00:48:44.716
It's an account ledger,
but it's in some kind of code.


639
00:48:44.924 --> 00:48:46.685
Look. These numbers
look like dates.


640
00:48:46.890 --> 00:48:48.584
I'm assuming these
are dollar amounts.


641
00:48:48.790 --> 00:48:52.553
But this middle column,
I don't know.


642
00:48:52.757 --> 00:48:54.882
They're too short
to be account numbers, right?


643
00:48:55.090 --> 00:49:00.614
- Could they be phone numbers?
- No. Badge numbers.


644
00:49:00.823 --> 00:49:01.914
Are you sure?

645
00:49:02.124 --> 00:49:06.181
Yeah. This is a record
of every cop who's on the payroll.


646
00:49:06.990 --> 00:49:09.218
Jesus, this thing goes back
at least 10 years.


647
00:49:09.424 --> 00:49:11.390
Is there any way
we can find names?


648
00:49:12.057 --> 00:49:14.546
If I still had access, which I don't..

649
00:49:15.990 --> 00:49:17.853
it could take days..

650
00:49:18.057 --> 00:49:20.818
possibly weeks to match
these badge numbers with names.


651
00:49:21.024 --> 00:49:24.354
Plus we don't have any evidence.
Everybody in here's a suspect.


652
00:49:24.558 --> 00:49:26.183
All right. A couple of weeks ago..

653
00:49:26.391 --> 00:49:28.254
Vaughn came over
with another man.


654
00:49:28.457 --> 00:49:31.650
It ended up in a shouting match
and I haven't seen Vaughn since..


655
00:49:31.857 --> 00:49:35.255
but after that John became
really paranoid about the book.


656
00:49:35.457 --> 00:49:37.514
He kept talking
about going to the DA.


657
00:49:37.723 --> 00:49:41.621
- And who was the other man?
- A Detective Vargas.


658
00:49:44.124 --> 00:49:45.454
Okay.

659
00:49:45.657 --> 00:49:47.850
Look. I need you
to write down the names..


660
00:49:48.057 --> 00:49:50.682
of every cop you talked to
since, including Vargas.


661
00:49:50.890 --> 00:49:52.220
Okay.

662
00:49:52.424 --> 00:49:54.390
Maybe I can get
their badge numbers.


663
00:50:21.957 --> 00:50:23.684
Charming neighborhood.

664
00:50:23.890 --> 00:50:27.516
- I been looking for a summer home.
- You got that list for me?


665
00:50:30.590 --> 00:50:34.250
Marty Pappas, Darrin Harris,
Jim Vargas.


666
00:50:34.457 --> 00:50:36.218
What do you need
with all these badges?


667
00:50:36.424 --> 00:50:39.685
I met with the wife.
Seems Mr. Norcut kept records.


668
00:50:39.890 --> 00:50:42.617
Every cop that's ever taken a cent
is written in a ledger..


669
00:50:42.823 --> 00:50:44.187
and listed by badge number.

670
00:50:44.391 --> 00:50:47.152
Jesus, Tom. What are you..?

671
00:50:47.357 --> 00:50:50.346
You know how many guys Vaughn
would send if he knew you had that?


672
00:50:50.557 --> 00:50:53.522
- Let me worry about that.
- Well, take my advice.


673
00:50:53.523 --> 00:50:56.689
- Forget you ever saw any ledger.
- Not that simple.


674
00:50:56.890 --> 00:50:59.186
Yeah, it is. Somebody asks,
you say, "What ledger?"


675
00:50:59.391 --> 00:51:04.346
- I'm in the ledger.
- Jesus Christ. So burn it.


676
00:51:05.291 --> 00:51:07.416
It's your motive. 
Get rid of it.

677
00:51:07.623 --> 00:51:10.589
- It's practically got a bow on it.
- Poor woman's husband's dead.


678
00:51:10.790 --> 00:51:13.086
Burn the thing that might help her
find the killer?


679
00:51:13.291 --> 00:51:15.154
What do you care?
She's some rich bitch..


680
00:51:15.357 --> 00:51:19.584
wearing a million-dollar blindfold.
Get the book, light a match.


681
00:51:20.457 --> 00:51:23.513
- Thanks, partner.
- What the fuck you call me?


682
00:51:25.291 --> 00:51:28.688
Partners stick together, huh?
Partners follow the plan.


683
00:51:28.890 --> 00:51:30.913
I told you sit tight,
you dig up some book..


684
00:51:31.124 --> 00:51:33.056
half the fucking city
will kill you for?


685
00:51:33.257 --> 00:51:36.689
- Walk away, Tom. Forget it.
- Walk away? I tried to walk away.


686
00:51:36.890 --> 00:51:38.515
From everything. 
From all this shit.

687
00:51:38.723 --> 00:51:41.746
- And look where I am.
- All the shit. Shit like me, right?


688
00:51:41.957 --> 00:51:44.718
You pick up the phone
for the first time in how long..


689
00:51:44.924 --> 00:51:47.515
and is it because you wanna
catch up or bullshit..


690
00:51:47.723 --> 00:51:50.587
and, you know, let me see
my goddaughter?


691
00:51:50.790 --> 00:51:54.620
