I didn't wanna cut you off,
man. I had to.


919
01:10:58.822 --> 01:11:02.310
Okay, I fucked up, all right?
Is that what you wanna hear?


920
01:11:02.522 --> 01:11:05.386
I just want my partner back, Tommy.

921
01:11:06.056 --> 01:11:09.852
Not for a day.
You know, not for one last thing.


922
01:11:10.056 --> 01:11:12.385
Back, man.

923
01:11:14.923 --> 01:11:20.049
- I'm back.
- Yeah? All right.


924
01:11:22.589 --> 01:11:26.681
All right, so let's shut up about that.
Where is she now?


925
01:11:26.889 --> 01:11:29.354
Talking to Vargas.
God knows what she's telling him.


926
01:11:29.556 --> 01:11:33.352
Can you get your hands on the book?
Then call Vargas, arrange a trade..


927
01:11:33.556 --> 01:11:35.454
give him the book,
he'll drop the case.


928
01:11:35.656 --> 01:11:39.748
No. We gotta go over his head. Cut
him off before he can make a case.


929
01:11:39.956 --> 01:11:42.319
- Cut him off with what?
- The truth.


930
01:11:42.522 --> 01:11:45.545
They're gonna wanna know how you
know, why you didn't come forward.


931
01:11:45.756 --> 01:11:48.916
- They're gonna be all over your ass.
- Well, she can back us up.


932
01:11:49.123 --> 01:11:51.953
What if she doesn't?
She's probably loyal to this guy.


933
01:11:52.156 --> 01:11:54.678
- That's a chance I'll have to take.
- Listen, Tom.


934
01:11:54.889 --> 01:11:57.377
The best shot we have
is with Vargas directly.


935
01:11:57.589 --> 01:12:00.078
I'll go with you. Make sure
he doesn't pull any shit.


936
01:12:00.289 --> 01:12:03.949
We could take care of this. The three
of us. We could do it tonight.


937
01:12:04.756 --> 01:12:06.722
I'll make the call.

938
01:12:07.322 --> 01:12:10.118
I gotta pick Rose up first.
Give me an hour.


939
01:12:10.322 --> 01:12:12.311
We can make the trade
at the old depot.


940
01:12:12.522 --> 01:12:15.386
He's back, ladies and gentlemen.
The old depot, in an hour.


941
01:12:15.589 --> 01:12:19.749
Hey.
What, I don't even get a goodbye?


942
01:12:21.123 --> 01:12:23.180
Bye, Eddie.

943
01:13:05.989 --> 01:13:10.683
- Ann. You all right?
- How did you get in?


944
01:13:12.856 --> 01:13:18.345
Of course. I'm actually fine.
It just keeps opening up.


945
01:13:18.556 --> 01:13:21.351
- So where you going?
- Nowhere.


946
01:13:21.556 --> 01:13:23.613
Why's your car packed?

947
01:13:26.422 --> 01:13:31.787
I know who this key belongs to,
and so do you.


948
01:13:36.255 --> 01:13:39.881
You really shouldn't be here. Vargas
is asking a lot of questions about you.


949
01:13:40.089 --> 01:13:42.281
Eddie Lorenzo was my partner.

950
01:13:42.489 --> 01:13:46.013
He was my friend. My best man.
He's my daughter's godfather.


951
01:13:46.222 --> 01:13:48.814
- Don't know what you're talking about.
- Stop lying to me.


952
01:13:49.023 --> 01:13:51.420
We need to go
to the police and tell them everything.


953
01:13:51.622 --> 01:13:56.078
Tell them what, Tom? It's a key.
So what? It could belong to anybody.


954
01:13:56.289 --> 01:13:59.221
And what about that baby?
Could that be anybody's too?


955
01:13:59.956 --> 01:14:01.945
Get out.

956
01:14:02.989 --> 01:14:05.147
Did you ask him to do it?
Is that what happened?


957
01:14:05.355 --> 01:14:09.083
He didn't do it. He'd never do that.
He told me that and I believe him.


958
01:14:09.289 --> 01:14:11.585
- Now get out, Tom.
- He's lying.


959
01:14:11.956 --> 01:14:16.082
Oh, go ahead. Call the police.
I'll just tell them you broke in.


960
01:14:16.522 --> 01:14:19.147
- I'm calling Eddie.
- Wait.


961
01:14:19.355 --> 01:14:22.219
If he still has his key, he's innocent.
And I'll go.


962
01:14:22.756 --> 01:14:24.381
- Just ask him.
- Please don't do this.


963
01:14:24.589 --> 01:14:25.577
Ask him.

964
01:14:25.956 --> 01:14:30.684
<i>- Please.
- Annie? Annie?</i>


965
01:14:31.622 --> 01:14:36.645
<i>- Annie, are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.</i>


966
01:14:36.856 --> 01:14:43.311
Hey, I was gonna ask you. Can you
give the key back, just in case?


967
01:14:45.622 --> 01:14:50.919
- Okay, good. Okay, no, that's all.
- Well?


968
01:14:53.122 --> 01:14:55.452
He already threw it away.

969
01:15:05.889 --> 01:15:10.378
You should've seen him, Tom.
He was so happy when I told him.


970
01:15:10.589 --> 01:15:15.715
He said it was a girl and he ran out
and bought all these presents.


971
01:15:16.255 --> 01:15:18.813
But I couldn't tell John.

972
01:15:19.455 --> 01:15:23.945
So I told Ed that I had a miscarriage,
but he didn't believe me.


973
01:15:24.155 --> 01:15:26.781
He thought John forced me.

974
01:15:27.122 --> 01:15:30.145
- We have to tell the police.
- No.


975
01:15:30.355 --> 01:15:34.754
Tom, just give me the key.
Nobody needs to know about this.


976
01:15:35.255 --> 01:15:38.017
If you go to the police,
I'll deny it and so will he.


977
01:15:38.589 --> 01:15:40.680
That's a chance I have to take.

978
01:15:40.889 --> 01:15:44.514
Tom, please don't be so naive.
We all have secrets.


979
01:15:47.088 --> 01:15:49.646
I'm tired of keeping secrets.

980
01:15:58.589 --> 01:16:02.419
I have to see someone. It may take a
while, so I need you to stay at Anita's.


981
01:16:02.889 --> 01:16:05.548
- I don't need a babysitter.
- I called. She's expecting you.


982
01:16:05.756 --> 01:16:09.244
- Dad.
- Look. No arguments, please?


983
01:16:10.956 --> 01:16:14.012
Hey, hey, hey. No hug?

984
01:16:19.556 --> 01:16:21.545
Love you.

985
01:16:35.155 --> 01:16:37.348
Yes, Detective Vargas, please.

986
01:17:12.656 --> 01:17:15.417
- Where's Lorenzo?
- He'll be here.


987
01:17:17.922 --> 01:17:19.548
Look, relax, Tom.

988
01:17:20.856 --> 01:17:25.220
We got three units covering the road
in. Two more down on the tracks.


989
01:17:25.422 --> 01:17:26.854
No way he's getting out of here.

990
01:17:34.289 --> 01:17:38.346
I know it doesn't feel like it right now,
but you're doing the right thing.


991
01:17:38.922 --> 01:17:41.081
He may be your buddy,
but he's made some mistakes.


992
01:17:41.689 --> 01:17:45.212
- Best to let the law handle it from here.
- Save that shit for the TV cameras.


993
01:17:45.422 --> 01:17:49.354
We both know why you're here.
You're saving Robert Vaughn's ass.


994
01:17:51.289 --> 01:17:53.255
Fair enough.

995
01:17:54.222 --> 01:17:57.120
You got that ledger?
We'll get Lorenzo.


996
01:17:57.322 --> 01:17:59.481
This goes away.
You go on with your life.


997
01:17:59.689 --> 01:18:03.849
- You'll get it when he's in custody.
- Fair enough, okay.


998
01:18:09.088 --> 01:18:11.350
Rose, I thought I told you
to go to Anita's.


999
01:18:11.556 --> 01:18:14.283
Oh, it's okay. I'm not alone.
Uncle Eddie's here.


1000
01:18:17.756 --> 01:18:20.051
- Put him on.
- Okay. Uncle Eddie?


1001
01:18:21.489 --> 01:18:26.421
Hey, Tom. Running a little late.
We need to talk.


1002
01:18:26.622 --> 01:18:31.179
Come alone.
Yeah, great. See you soon.


1003
01:18:39.088 --> 01:18:41.577
Tom, where you going?

1004
01:18:56.255 --> 01:18:59.278
- Hey, here he is.
- Hey, Dad.


1005
01:18:59.988 --> 01:19:03.920
- Rosie insisted on making dinner.
- Rose, I want you to go next door.


1006
01:19:05.088 --> 01:19:06.714
Now.

1007
01:19:07.255 --> 01:19:09.221
I got one ready for you.

1008
01:19:10.255 --> 01:19:12.380
- Dad.
- That's okay, Rosie. Take it easy.


1009
01:19:13.055 --> 01:19:15.578
Everything's all right. He just had
a hard week at work.


1010
01:19:15.789 --> 01:19:18.879
We're gonna sit, have dinner,
talk things over so everybody knows..


1011
01:19:19.088 --> 01:19:22.213
what's going on here.
- Next door, Rose. Now.


1012
01:19:25.589 --> 01:19:28.077
All you had to do was show up,
do your job and go home.


1013
01:19:28.289 --> 01:19:30.152
- I had it all figured out.
- You set me up.


1014
01:19:30.355 --> 01:19:33.014
I had you protected.
I was protecting both of you.


1015
01:19:33.222 --> 01:19:36.188
- I couldn't let her come and see that.
- You call this protection?


1016
01:19:36.389 --> 01:19:39.014
I needed you to back off.
You know, I'm sorry.


1017
01:19:39.222 --> 01:19:41.745
- I should have known better.
- Come on, let's go.


1018
01:19:41.955 --> 01:19:45.353
What are you doing to me? Wait.
Listen, we could still do this.


1019
01:19:45.955 --> 01:19:49.285
Get Vargas on the phone. We can
hammer out some kind of angle.


1020
01:19:49.489 --> 01:19:53.784
- I don't work like that anymore.
- You take some oath as a janitor?


1021
01:19:54.556 --> 01:19:56.545
Stop it.

1022
01:19:57.055 --> 01:20:00.044
Okay. I see how it is now.
Anything goes when it's good for you.


1023
01:20:00.255 --> 01:20:03.744
But when I need help?
Where was that conscience of yours..


1024
01:20:03.955 --> 01:20:07.785
when Daniel Hill was bleeding
to death in the prison yard, huh?


1025
01:20:08.355 --> 01:20:10.685
That keep you up too?

1026
01:20:12.055 --> 01:20:14.953
No, you were fucking
sleeping like a baby.


1027
01:20:24.589 --> 01:20:26.612
Check your loyalties, buddy.

1028
01:20:26.821 --> 01:20:29.310
- You owe me.
- Put the gun away, Eddie.


1029
01:20:29.522 --> 01:20:33.147
Norcut was a fucking murderer.
Period.


1030
01:20:33.355 --> 01:20:37.515
- Who'd he kill, Eddie? Nobody.
- No, not nobody. He made her do it.


1031
01:20:39.721 --> 01:20:42.051
- He made her kill her own baby.
- She lied to you.


1032
01:20:42.255 --> 01:20:45.312
You think I can't have
what you have?


1033
01:20:45.522 --> 01:20:48.181
She was gonna have our child,
but he bought her off.


1034
01:20:48.389 --> 01:20:51.184
Just like he buys everybody off.
He tried to buy me off.


1035
01:20:51.389 --> 01:20:53.877
- Put the piece away.
- Remember that night I went there?


1036
01:20:54.088 --> 01:20:56.918
He tried to write a check
so I would leave.


1037
01:20:58.155 --> 01:21:00.485
A check.

1038
01:21:03.556 --> 01:21:06.953
She was gonna have a baby with me.
Tommy, with me.


1039
01:21:07.355 --> 01:21:11.287
- She was gonna have our child.
- Stop waving your gun in my house.


1040
01:21:14.489 --> 01:21:17.011
She was gonna have our child.

1041
01:21:19.022 --> 01:21:23.011
I had no choice.
Man is allowed to do anything..


1042
01:21:23.222 --> 01:21:26.382
if he's protecting his family.
You know I'm right, Tom.


1043
01:21:29.855 --> 01:21:32.083
Still family here?

1044
01:21:33.389 --> 01:21:35.548
We still family?

1045
01:21:40.155 --> 01:21:42.144
It's over, Eddie.

1046
01:21:43.721 --> 01:21:45.880
Oh, God.

1047
01:21:47.556 --> 01:21:50.021
Who's gonna clean you up, Tom?

1048
01:23:04.222 --> 01:23:08.518
Thanks. I'll burn this book
and we'll all sleep better.


1049
01:23:21.755 --> 01:23:25.347
Go on, Tom. We'll clean this up.

1050
01:23:30.721 --> 01:23:32.710
<i>Most people don't know this.</i>

1051
01:23:32.922 --> 01:23:36.581
<i>But when someone dies
in your house and leaves a mess..</i>


1052
01:23:37.088 --> 01:23:40.213
<i>it's up to the
family to clean it up.</i>

1053
01:23:40.988 --> 01:23:44.647
<i>Most people don't have the stomach
for that kind of thing.</i>


1054
01:23:45.222 --> 01:23:47.347
<i>That's where my dad comes in.</i>

1055
01:23:49.588 --> 01:23:52.850
<i>My dad says
that stains have memories.</i>


1056
01:23:53.322 --> 01:23:58.720
<i>They remember their shape,
their color, their smell.</i>


1057
01:24:00.255 --> 01:24:05.153
<i>And the really deep ones
return again and again.</i>


1058
01:24:10.389 --> 01:24:16.844
<i>With these stains, it's easier
to start over than to try cleaning them.</i>


1059
01:24:18.788 --> 01:24:23.686
<i>Sometimes you have a choice.
Sometimes you don't.</i>


1060
01:24:25.621 --> 01:24:29.247
<i>All you can do is hope.</i>